  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CHHIP - Primary School Comprehensive Health and Hygiene Improvement Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CHHIP is a health education and improvement program with three interrelated components designed for implementation into the primary schools of the Darjeeling District in West Bengal, India.  It was created to address the concerns and deficiencies revealed through the above discussed assessment.  CHHIP is designed so that participating students and schools not only gain essential knowledge pertaining to their personal health and hygiene, but will benefit from a comprehensive program to improve the overall learning environment, provide early intervention for health issues, and equip children with critical life-skills, enabling them to take control of their own personal development and improve the health of their communities as agents of change.  
There are three main components of CHHIP, which include:

Health Education Curriculum 	
Health Monitoring and Early Intervention
Structural Improvement of School Health Environment</narrative>
  </description>
